    "comments": [
      {
        "id": 45557,
        "summary": "Deprecated",
        "content": "Technically both <a href=\"https://mushroomobserver.org/lookups/lookup_name/Amanita+muscaria+var.+flavivolvata\"><i>Amanita muscaria var. flavivolvata</i></a> and <a href=\"https://mushroomobserver.org/lookups/lookup_name/Amanita+muscaria+subsp.+flavivolvata\"><i>Amanita muscaria subsp. flavivolvata</i></a> are valid. However, to ensure that we aren&#8217;t exporting both to third parties like EOL, I&#8217;m suggesting that we prefer the subspecies. This follows what Rod is currently doing on Amanitaceae.org and I believe there is good evidence that this is a distinct species that will eventually be published as <a href=\"https://mushroomobserver.org/lookups/lookup_name/Amanita+amerimuscaria\"><i>Amanita amerimuscaria</i></a>. Given this subspecies status seems more appropriate than a variety.",
        "created_at": "2011-12-13T14:57:29.000Z",
        "updated_at": "2011-12-13T14:57:29.000Z",
        "owner": {
          "id": 1,
          "login_name": "nathan",
          "legal_name": "Nathan Wilson"
        }
      }
    ]
  },
